                          </div>
                          <p id="fs-idp139124096">
                            Likewise, the molecular mass of an aspirin molecule, C
                            <sub>9</sub>H
                            <sub>8</sub>O
                            <sub>4</sub>, is the sum of the atomic masses of nine carbon atoms, eight hydrogen atoms, and four oxygen atoms, which amounts to 180.15 amu (
                            <a
                              class="autogenerated-content"
                              href="#CNX_Chem_03_01_aspirin"
                            >Figure 3.3</a>).
