                              <span data-type="title">Check Your Learning</span>
                              Calcium phosphate, Ca
                              <sub>3</sub>(PO
                              <sub>4</sub>)
                              <sub>2</sub>, is an ionic compound and a common anti-caking agent added to food products. What is the formula mass (amu) of calcium phosphate?
                            </p>
                            <div data-type="note" id="fs-idm5833232">
